						               													<description>Get set for a great trip across the U.S.A.! You don't have to worry about what to bring or what to wear. So don't drag out the backpacks or knapsacks, and forget about the plane, train, and bus tickets. You won't even need a driver's license. All you will need for the journey is THE ACROSS THE USA GAME book and a few playful, game-loving friends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With this great game you'll travel from coast to coast, exploring all fifty states and discovering all sorts of interesting info about this wonderful land of ours. You'll find out about national parks and rivers, famous monuments and landmarks, prominent people, state capitals, flowers, and birds - tons of terrific trivia. When your cross-country game is finished, you will have had a fun-filled time from sea to shining sea - and what better souvenir of an unforgettable trip!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- from inside cover&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game was sold as a slim staple-bound book. The map gameboard is on the center pages, with a list of basic facts about each US state on the backs of the gameboard pages. The surrounding pages contain a total of 32 punch-out trivia cards, each with 8 questions on the front and 8 answers on the back. The rules are inside the back cover. Players must provide their own playing pieces and a die.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- user description&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
